===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|ilke|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|ilca||lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*ilīkaz}}, a compound of {{m|gem-pro|*iz}} and {{m|gem-pro|*-līkaz}} from the noun {{m|gem-pro|*līką||body}}.

The sense of “type”, “kind” is from the application of the phrase ‘{{term|of that ilk}}’ to families: the word thus came to mean ‘{{term|family}}’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪlk/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-ilk.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
